AV-45 PET Scan Information

Source: R/data.R
AV45META.Rd

AV-45 PET Scan Information data. More information is available at https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Usage

data(AV45META)

Format

A data frame with 3400 observations and 52 variables.

Source

https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Details

  • ORIGPROT character Original study protocol , with options: ADNI1, ADNIGO, ADNI2

  • COLPROT factor Study protocol of data collection , with factor levels: ADNI1, ADNIGO, ADNI2, ADNI3, ADNI4

  • ID numeric Range value: 8, ..., 6410

  • PTID character Participant ID

  • RID numeric Participant roster ID Range value: 2, ..., 5296

  • SITEID numeric Site ID Range value: 1, ..., 61

  • VISCODE character Visit code

  • VISCODE2 character Translated visit code

  • USERDATE Date Date record created Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • USERDATE2 Date Date record last updated Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • RECNO numeric Range value: 1, ..., 3

  • PMCONDCT character Was the scan conducted? 1=Yes;0=No Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMREASON character Reason why the scan was not conducted:

    • ADNIGO: 1=Illness;2=Participant unavailable;3=Participant unwilling;4=Administrative problems;5=Withdrawn consent;6=Other (specify)

    • ADNI2: 1=Illness;2=Participant unavailable;3=Participant unwilling;4=Administrative problems;8=Software/scanner error; 5=Withdrawn consent;7=Not called for by the protocol;6=Other (specify)

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • RADTRACER character If no, was radiotracer administered? 1=Yes;0=No Decoded Value: Yes

  • EXAMDATE Date Examination Date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • PMSCANNER character GE 1=check here Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMGEMODEL character If GE, Scanner Model:

    • ADNIGO: 1=Advance;2=Discovery LS;3=Discovery ST;4=Discovery RX;5=Discovery STE/VCT

    • ADNI2: 1=Advance;2=Discovery LS;3=Discovery ST;4=Discovery RX;5=Discovery STE/VCT; 6=Discovery 600; 7=Discovery 690

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMSIEMENS character Siemens 1=check here Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMSIEMODEL character If Siemens, Scanner Model: 1=ACCEL/EXACT;2=Biograph (Model 1023/1024);7=Biograph HiRes (Model 1080);3=BioGraph TruePoint (Model 1093/1094);4=BioGraph mCT;5=HR+;6=HRRT Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMPHILLIPS character Phillips 1=check here Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMPHMODEL character If Phillips, Scanner Model: 1=Allegro;2=Gemini;3=Gemini-GXL;4=Gemini-TF Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMQCTIME character Time of today's Scanner QC

  • PMFDGTIME character Time of Florbetapir F18 dose assay

  • PMFDGDOS numeric Florbetapir F18 dose assay Range value: 0.4, ..., 98

  • PMFDGVOL numeric Florbetapir F18 Volume Range value: 0, ..., 97

  • PMINJTIME character Time of Florbetapir F18 injection

  • PMSCTIME character Standard Emission Scan Start Time

  • PMVARIAT character Any variations from protocol during Florbetapir F18 uptake? 1=Yes; 0=No Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMPROTID character Predefined Acquisition Protocol ID

  • PMFRAME numeric For the standard late acquisition, which framing rate was used?

    • ADNIGO: 1=4 frames, 5 min/frame (4x300s);2=2 scans, 10 min each (2x600s) (only for BioGraph scanners without list-mode)

    • ADNI2: 1=4 frames, 5 min/frame (4x300s);2=2 scans, 10 min each (2x600s) (only for BioGraph scanners without list-mode);3=1 frame, 20 min (1x1200s) (only for the oldest BioGraph scanners: Models 1023 or 1024)

  • PMDEVIAT character If any deviations, describe:

  • PMMOTION character Subject motion problems: 1=Yes;0=No Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMMALFUN character Scanner malfunction 1=Yes;0=No Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMOTHER character Other protocol variations: 1=Yes;0=No Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMRECON character Check which of the following reconstructions was used:

    • ADNIGO: 2=FORE/2D-OSEM (Siemens);4=OSEM3D (Siemens) (If HHRT scanners using OP, please select OSEM3D);5=3D Iterative (GE);1=3D-Ramla (Philips);3=3D Back-projection (GE)

    • ADNI2: 2=FORE/2D-OSEM (Siemens);4=OSEM3D (Siemens) (If HHRT scanners using OP, please select OSEM3D);5=3D Iterative (GE);6=FORE Iterative (GE); 1=3D or LOR Ramla (Philips);3=3D Back-projection (GE)

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMSUBSET character # subsets:

    • ADNIGO: 14=14;16=16;20=20;99=Other

    • ADNI2: 12=12;14=14;16=16;20=20;21=21;24=24;32=32;99=Other

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMSUBSPE numeric If Other, specify: Range value: 12, ..., 32

  • PMITERAT character # iterations: 4=4;6=6;99=Other Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMITERSPE logical If Other, specify: Boolean value: TRUE/ FALSE

  • PMRAMLA numeric If 3D or LOR Ramla, Lambda= Range value: 0.008, ..., 1

  • PMSHARP character Was 'Smooth' parameter set to 'Sharp'? 1=Check here to confirm Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMFILTER character If 3D Back-Projection, Ramp filter? 1=Check here to confirm Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMMODEON character If FORE/2D-OSEM select one of the following:

    • ADNIGO: 1=Brain Mode "ON" for PET-only Siemens scanners;2=TRIM "ON" for PET/CT Siemens scanners (older software versions); 3=TRIM not available for PET/CT scanners (new software versions)

    • ADNI2: 1=Brain Mode 'ON' for PET-only Siemens scanners;2=TRIM 'ON' for PET/CT Siemens scanners (older software versions); 3=TRIM not available for PET/CT scanners (new software versions)

    Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMSMOOTH character No post-process smoothing: 1=Check here to confirm Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMATTEN character Attenuation Correction: 1=CT; 2=Ge-68+Segmentation;3=Cs-137+Segmentation Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMTRNSFR character Was data transferred to LONI within 24 hours of scan? 1=Yes;0=No Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMTRNDATE character Transfer Date

  • PMTRNDATEYR_DRVD numeric Transfer Year (Derived from PMTRNDATE) Range value: 2001, ..., 2017

  • PMARCHIVE character Was all raw PET data archived locally to be able to do complete reconstruction of PET Scan if needed? 1=Yes;0=No Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMLPDONE character Was a Lumbar Puncture completed prior to the Florbetapir F18 scan? 1=Yes;0=No Decoded Value: Yes

  • PMLPINTER character If Yes, What was the interval between LP and Florbetapir F18? 1=less than 6 hours;2=6-12 hours;3=13-24 hours;4=25-48 hours;5=49-72 hours;6=more than 72 hours Decoded Value: Yes

  • update_stamp POSIXct POSIXct: YYY-MM-DD
